headline: S&P Futures Tick Higher With Focus on U.S. Retail Sales Data and Trump-Putin Meeting
summary: September S&P 500 E-Mini futures (ESU25) are trending up +0.17% this morning, bolstered by continued hopes for a Federal Reserve rate cut next month, while investors await U.S. retail sales data and high-stakes talks between U.S. President Donald Trump and Russia’s Vladimir Putin.
